planation":"\u003Cp\u003EPrecision medicine is an emerging approach to healthcare that considers individual variability in genes, environment, and lifestyle. The primary goal of precision medicine involves \u003Cstrong\u003Ecustomising medical decisions based on individual genetic profiles\u003C/strong\u003E. This approach integrates genetic information, environmental factors, and lifestyle data to optimise treatment selection and dosing for each patient.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReducing healthcare costs through standardised treatments\u003C/strong\u003E - Precision medicine actually moves away from standardised approaches towards personalised care\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDeveloping new pharmaceutical compounds\u003C/strong\u003E - While drug development may benefit from precision medicine insights, this is not its primary goal\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEliminating the need for clinical trials\u003C/strong\u003E - Clinical trials remain essential for establishing treatment safety and efficacy\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReplacing traditional diagnostic methods\u003C/strong\u003E - Precision medicine complements rather than replaces traditional diagnostics\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPrecision medicine aims to improve patient outcomes by matching the right treatment to the right patient at the right time, taking into account their unique genetic and molecular characteristics.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Precision medicine uses genetic and molecular information to guide personalised treatment decisions.","Pharmacogenetic testing helps predict drug responses based on genetic variations.","Individual genetic differences can significantly impact drug metabolism 